            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "# Proposal\n\n- Arbitrary modes can be created, called \"user modes\". `nvim_def_mode(ns: string, ??)`\n- Modes can be stacked/nested. Entering a new user-mode adds to the current \"stack\" of modes.\n    - User-modes inherit the current \"builtin\" mode (normal/visual/etc).\n- Each mode \"scope\" is a namespace. (side-note: the idea that namespaces can define new \"scopes\" will also be useful for extending events/autocmds.)\n- `:umap` (\"user mode\") (or `:emap` (\"extended mode\")? `:pmap`?)\n  ```\n  umap <namespace-id> ...\n  ```\n- Delete the namespace to teardown the mode?\n- `mode()` returns its usual value + `u`. E.g. in normal-mode during a user-defined mode, `mode() => \"nu\"`.\n    - `mode(…, v:true): string[]` returns the \"stack\" of user-mode namespaces.\n- `ModeChanged` event signals a user-mode, same as builtin modes.\n\n\n## Use cases\n\n- completion mode https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/3949\n- snippet mode https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/26449",
